data.description: The Alum Rock Public Library in partnership with MathAndCoding presents this special introductory Python Programming class for students in 5th grade and above. Python is a very popular programming language and is one of the easiest languages to learn. In this four-week workshop, you will learn all the fundamental concepts of Python like variables, operators, conditionals, loops, functions, dictionaries, and lists. At the end of the course, you would have learned how to develop sophisticated programs and games using Python. Register only if you can attend all the sessions (January 7, 14, 21, & 28) of this workshop as each session builds on the concepts learned in the previous sessions. For questions or more information, please call the information desk at 408-808-3090.
data.name: Python Coding Basics by Diana Learned
